news.title: Sunac China proposes deleveraging plan to restructure debt
news.para: Sunac is one of the biggest property developers in China that has been reeling under debt woes. The company last month proposed a plan to restructure and extend its onshore debts.

news.title: Elan Group raises $60 million from PAG for construction of realty projects, growth
news.para: The investment will be used towards growth capital to endorse existing debt and to scale up construction of its new luxury housing project -- "The Presidential", located in Sector 106 Gurugram.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body plans new funding for two metro corridors
news.para: The logic the GDA has put forth is that no state development authority is bearing the whole cost of a metro project and the same formula should be applied to these two Ghaziabad metro extension projects as well.

news.title: Chandigarh estate office demolishes illegal structures in Daria village
news.para: Notices have been issued by the area SDM. An official said that the demolition drives would continue. Over the past one month, the department has stepped up the drive against illegal structures.

news.title: Noida yet to collect 50% of stamp dues target this financial year
news.para: The district administration has now decided to conduct an awareness drive among residents to register their flats before moving in - an attempt to generate more revenue.

news.title: Old, illegal colonies in 413 towns of Madhya Pradesh to be legalized, says CM
news.para: "Today, we have decided to legalize old, illegal colonies in 413 cities of Madhya Pradesh by simplifying rules and charging minimum fee. I won't allow any new illegal colony to be developed," he said.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation inching towards meeting property tax target
news.para: While it collected 165 crore at the end of 2021-22 fiscal, the civic body has already collected 151 crore or 44% of the tax target.

news.title: Over 240 fined in two months for GRAP violations in Gurugram
news.para: At 111, the highest number of challans have been issued for keeping construction materials uncovered. The challans amounting to Rs 11.6 lakh have been issued.

news.title: Maharashtra cooperation department against repealing MOFA: Minister
news.para: The minister said the department was of the view that the Act was in the interest of the homebuyers and can co-exist with the central Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) Act in the state.

news.title: Arbitrary upkeep fees? Development agencies and DM can take a call now in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: While the power to decide on any dispute would lie with the development authority and district magistrate, the developer would preside over the formation of any new RWA following the Uttar Pradesh Apartment Act of 2010.

news.title: Noida: No zoning regulations in YEIDA master plan
news.para: Given the immense scope of industrial development in the region owing to the upcoming Noida International Airport in Jewar and mega projects like Film City, Medical Device Park and Data Park, officials said, the Authority plans to keep its sectors for development "as and when required".

news.title: Maintenance against property must be written in gift deed: Supreme Court
news.para: A bench of Justices Sanjay K Kaul and A S Oka gave this practical advice on Tuesday to senior citizens, who generally gift self-earned properties to their children in the understanding, hope and expectation that they would be well looked after in their sunset years when ailments routinely affect them.

news.title: SC quashes attachment of VGN Projects Estates' 10.6-acre land by ED under PMLA
news.para: The attachment order was passed on the basis of an allegation that the property was sold less than the guideline value of ₹387 crore causing a loss of ₹115 crore to HTL, a government of India undertaking.

news.title: Gururgam: Greenopolis buyers protest as flats not ready even after 11 years
news.para: During a protest at the Gurgaon office of the Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (H-Rera) on Wednesday, the homebuyers alleged that one of the two developers - Orris Infrastructure - has utilised all money collected from them but "the project is still incomplete".

news.title: Order granting bail to DHFL's promoters not to be given effect to till Feb 1: Delhi HC
news.para: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) has challenged the trial court's order granting statutory bail to Wadhawan brothers because of "incomplete charge sheet".
